---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
---

<Layout title="Methodology — GitHacker" description="How the benchmark and security harnesses work.">
  <article class="max-w-[820px] mx-auto px-6 pt-10 pb-16">

    <header class="mb-6">
      <p class="smallcaps text-[12px] text-[var(--ink-mute)]" data-i18n="m.preTitle">Methodology</p>
      <h1 class="mt-1 text-[28px] leading-[1.2]" data-i18n="m.title">Benchmark and security harness design</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-[14.5px] text-[var(--ink-soft)] leading-relaxed" data-i18n="m.intro">
        The
        <a href="/benchmark" class="underline">Benchmark</a>
        and
        <a href="/security" class="underline">Security</a>
        pages report results.  This page documents how those numbers
        are produced — the test corpus, the harness, the metrics, and
        the threat model — so the figures can be read with the right
        priors.
      </p>
    </header>

    <SectionHeading n={1} id="principles"><span data-i18n="m.s1H">Design principles</span></SectionHeading>
    <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7]" data-i18n="m.s1B">
      The harness is designed around three principles. <strong>Fairness</strong>:
      every tool receives the same target served by the same web-server
      instance, with the same starting state. <strong>Completeness</strong>:
      evaluation covers all recoverable Git artifacts (source code,
      reflogs, stashes, commits, branches, remotes, tags), not just whether
      a clone succeeds. <strong>Reproducibility</strong>: the test
      repository is generated from a fixed random seed, and every
      component — tool images, server containers, scoring code — is
      version-controlled.
    </p>

    <SectionHeading n={2} id="test-repo"><span data-i18n="m.s2H">Test repository</span></SectionHeading>
    <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7]" data-i18n="m.s2B">
      A ground-truth Git repository is generated programmatically
      (<a href="https://github.com/WangYihang/GitHacker/blob/main/benchmark/generate.py" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline"><code>benchmark/generate.py</code></a>,
      seed&nbsp;=&nbsp;0).  It contains 2–16 random commits, 2–8 random
      branches, 15 well-known branches (<code>master</code>, <code>main</code>,
      <code>dev</code>, <code>release</code>, …), up to 16 semantic-version
      tags, 2–16 stashes, files in both the staging area and working
      directory, and a PHP LFI script.  A <em>manifest</em> categorises
      every file by feature, which is what makes the per-feature
      accuracy column on the benchmark page meaningful.
    </p>

    <SectionHeading n={3} id="scenarios"><span data-i18n="m.s3H">Web-server scenarios</span></SectionHeading>
    <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7]" data-i18n="m.s3B">
      The repository is served over HTTP under five configurations,
      each a Docker Compose service
      (<a href="https://github.com/WangYihang/GitHacker/tree/main/test/docker" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline"><code>test/docker/</code></a>):
    </p>
    <ol class="mt-2 ml-5 list-decimal text-[14px] leading-relaxed space-y-1" data-i18n="m.s3L">
      <li><strong>Apache httpd</strong> with <code>DirectoryIndex</code> enabled (directory listing on)</li>
      <li><strong>Apache httpd</strong> with <code>Options -Indexes</code> (directory listing off)</li>
      <li><strong>Nginx</strong> with <code>autoindex on</code></li>
      <li><strong>Nginx</strong> with <code>autoindex off</code> (default)</li>
      <li><strong>PHP 7.2 + Apache</strong> with a Local File Inclusion entry point</li>
    </ol>

    <SectionHeading n={4} id="tool-execution"><span data-i18n="m.s4H">Tool execution</span></SectionHeading>
    <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7]" data-i18n="m.s4B">
      Each tool runs in its own Docker container
      (<a href="https://github.com/WangYihang/GitHacker/tree/main/benchmark/tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline"><code>benchmark/tools/</code></a>)
      behind a unified interface (<code>run.sh &lt;url&gt; &lt;output-dir&gt;</code>).
      A 300-second timeout is enforced.  The server is restarted before
      each run so the access-log line count (one of the metrics) is
      directly attributable to the tool under test.
    </p>

    <SectionHeading n={5} id="metrics"><span data-i18n="m.s5H">Scoring metrics</span></SectionHeading>
    <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7]" data-i18n="m.s5B">
      Recovered files are compared against the manifest via MD5
      checksums (<a href="https://github.com/WangYihang/GitHacker/blob/main/benchmark/compare.py" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline"><code>benchmark/compare.py</code></a>).
      The four reported metrics are:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-2 ml-5 list-disc text-[14px] leading-relaxed space-y-1" data-i18n="m.s5L">
      <li><strong>Recovery Rate</strong> = correct files / total files (per feature, and aggregate)</li>
      <li><strong>Feature Support</strong> = binary, per feature, per (tool, scenario)</li>
      <li><strong>Duration</strong> = wall-clock seconds from container start to first idle</li>
      <li><strong>HTTP Requests</strong> = server log line count attributable to the tool</li>
    </ul>

    <SectionHeading n={6} id="threat-model"><span data-i18n="m.s6H">Threat model (security suite)</span></SectionHeading>
    <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7]" data-i18n="m.s6B">
      The security suite inverts the benchmark assumption: the
      pillager is the victim.  Each test is a malicious <code>.git/</code>
      crafted to attack the tool during recovery — code execution
      via <code>core.fsmonitor</code>, arbitrary file write via path
      traversal, SSRF via redirect, and known Git CVEs delivered as
      submodules or LFS objects.  A test is a <strong>FAIL</strong>
      if the malicious server attains code execution, arbitrary file
      write, or SSRF against the tool's container during recovery; a
      <strong>PASS</strong> if the tool refused or contained the
      payload.  Findings against unpatched tools are anonymized in
      <a href="/security" class="underline">Security</a> as
      <em>Tool&nbsp;A…F</em> until coordinated disclosure completes.
    </p>

    <SectionHeading n={7} id="environment"><span data-i18n="m.s7H">Environment</span></SectionHeading>
    <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7]" data-i18n="m.s7B">
      Results on this site are produced by the harness running on
      Linux + Docker.  Each run records its harness commit, generation
      timestamp, and random seed into the JSON output, so any plot you
      see can be traced to an exact reproducible configuration.  The
      benchmark also runs weekly via
      <a href="https://github.com/WangYihang/GitHacker/actions" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline">GitHub Actions</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-7 text-[13.5px]" data-i18n="m.footer">
      Reproduce instructions: <a href="/reproduce" class="underline">/reproduce</a>.
    </p>

  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    const M_ZH = {
      'm.preTitle': '方法论',
      'm.title':    '基准与安全测试框架的设计',
      'm.intro':    '<a href="/benchmark" class="underline">Benchmark</a> 与 <a href="/security" class="underline">Security</a> 两页呈现结果。本页说明这些数字是如何产生的 —— 测试集、harness、指标、威胁模型 —— 让读者以正确的先验解读图表。',
      'm.s1H': '设计原则',
      'm.s1B': 'harness 围绕三条原则构建：<strong>公平性</strong>—— 所有工具收到同一个目标，由同一台 Web 服务器实例提供，起始状态完全相同；<strong>完整性</strong>—— 评估覆盖全部可恢复的 Git 制品（源代码、reflogs、stashes、commits、branches、remotes、tags），不仅是 clone 是否成功；<strong>可复现性</strong>—— 测试仓库由固定随机种子生成，所有组件（工具镜像、服务器容器、评分代码）都进入版本控制。',
      'm.s2H': '测试仓库',
      'm.s2B': '通过程序化方式生成 ground-truth Git 仓库（<a href="https://github.com/WangYihang/GitHacker/blob/main/benchmark/generate.py" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline"><code>benchmark/generate.py</code></a>，seed&nbsp;=&nbsp;0）。仓库包含 2–16 个随机 commit、2–8 个随机分支、15 个常见分支名（<code>master</code>、<code>main</code>、<code>dev</code>、<code>release</code>、…）、最多 16 个语义化版本 tag、2–16 个 stash、暂存区与工作目录文件、以及一个 PHP LFI 脚本。生成的 <em>manifest</em> 按 feature 分类所有文件 —— 这是 benchmark 页面"按 feature 准确率"列得以有意义的根本原因。',
      'm.s3H': 'Web 服务器场景',
      'm.s3B': '仓库在五种 HTTP 配置下提供服务，每个场景是一个 Docker Compose 服务（<a href="https://github.com/WangYihang/GitHacker/tree/main/test/docker" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline"><code>test/docker/</code></a>）：',
      'm.s3L': '<li><strong>Apache httpd</strong>，<code>DirectoryIndex</code> 启用（目录列表开）</li><li><strong>Apache httpd</strong>，<code>Options -Indexes</code>（目录列表关）</li><li><strong>Nginx</strong>，<code>autoindex on</code></li><li><strong>Nginx</strong>，<code>autoindex off</code>（默认）</li><li><strong>PHP 7.2 + Apache</strong>，本地文件包含（LFI）入口</li>',
      'm.s4H': '工具执行',
      'm.s4B': '每个工具在独立的 Docker 容器中运行（<a href="https://github.com/WangYihang/GitHacker/tree/main/benchmark/tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline"><code>benchmark/tools/</code></a>），统一接口 <code>run.sh &lt;url&gt; &lt;output-dir&gt;</code>。超时 300 秒。每次运行前重启服务器，以便访问日志行数（其中一项指标）可直接归因于被测工具。',
      'm.s5H': '评分指标',
      'm.s5B': '通过 MD5 校验和对比恢复的文件（<a href="https://github.com/WangYihang/GitHacker/blob/main/benchmark/compare.py" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline"><code>benchmark/compare.py</code></a>）。四项指标：',
      'm.s5L': '<li><strong>恢复率</strong> = 正确文件 / 总文件（按 feature 和汇总两种粒度）</li><li><strong>功能支持</strong> = 按 feature 二值判定，按 (工具, 场景) 划分</li><li><strong>耗时</strong> = 容器启动到首次空闲的墙钟秒数</li><li><strong>HTTP 请求数</strong> = 归属于该工具的服务器日志行数</li>',
      'm.s6H': '威胁模型（安全套件）',
      'm.s6B': '安全套件反转 benchmark 的假设：pillager 是受害者。每个测试是一个精心构造的恶意 <code>.git/</code>，在恢复过程中攻击工具 —— 通过 <code>core.fsmonitor</code> 触发代码执行、通过路径穿越实现任意文件写入、通过重定向引发 SSRF、以及作为子模块或 LFS 对象投递的已知 Git CVE。若恶意服务器在恢复期间对工具容器达成代码执行、任意文件写入或 SSRF，则该测试记为 <strong>FAIL</strong>；若工具拒绝或限制 payload，则为 <strong>PASS</strong>。针对尚未修复工具的发现，在 <a href="/security" class="underline">Security</a> 中以 <em>Tool&nbsp;A…F</em> 匿名化，直至协调披露完成。',
      'm.s7H': '运行环境',
      'm.s7B': '本站结果由 Linux + Docker 下运行的 harness 产出。每次运行将其 harness commit、生成时间戳、随机种子写入 JSON 输出，使你看到的任一图表都能追溯至确切的可复现配置。Benchmark 也通过 <a href="https://github.com/WangYihang/GitHacker/actions" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline">GitHub Actions</a> 每周自动运行。',
      'm.footer': '复现说明见 <a href="/reproduce" class="underline">/reproduce</a>。',
    };
    window.addEventListener('langchange', (e) => {
      const lang = e.detail;
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-i18n^="m."]').forEach((el) => {
        const key = el.dataset.i18n;
        if (lang === 'en') {
          if (el.dataset.i18nOriginal) el.innerHTML = el.dataset.i18nOriginal;
          return;
        }
        if (!(key in M_ZH)) return;
        if (!el.dataset.i18nOriginal) el.dataset.i18nOriginal = el.innerHTML;
        el.innerHTML = M_ZH[key];
      });
    });
  </script>
</Layout>
